SeaWorld Orlando

SeaWorld Orlando is a world-class marine-themed amusement park that offers a captivating blend of entertainment, education, and conservation. With exhilarating rides, mesmerizing live shows, and interactive encounters with marine animals like dolphins, sharks, and penguins, it provides a unique and immersive experience for visitors of all ages. Guests can embark on thrilling roller coasters, enjoy live shows, and learn about marine life conservation efforts. From educational presentations to behind-the- scenes tours, SeaWorld Orlando aims to inspire a deeper appreciation for the wonders of the ocean and the importance of protecting marine ecosystems. It is a must-visit destination for those seeking adventure, entertainment, and a connection with the marine world.

Busch Gardens Tampa

As Florida’s thrill ride leader, Busch Gardens ® Tampa Bay is the ultimate family adventure, combining exciting seasonal events, incredible animal experiences, world-class roller coasters and more! Guests can take on a top-rated list of favorite attractions for thrill seekers, including Iron Gwazi, North America’s tallest and the world’s fastest and steepest hybrid coaster and winner of the Golden Ticket Award for the Best New Roller Coaster in 2022. Animal fans can connect with over 200 species of animals from around the world as they stroll through the park and upgrade their day with exclusive experiences, including hand-feeding giraffe on the park’s 65-acre Serengeti Plain.

Aquatica Orlando

It’s clear why Aquatica Orlando has been voted America’s #1 Outdoor Water Park. From high-speed slides and refreshing wave pools to pristine beaches, this splashy escape has something for guests of all ages. It’s home to some of the world’s most thrilling water rides, including the most slides in Orlando. The new Reef Plunge offers an eye-opening descent through a marine habitat, while Riptide Race offers the chance to challenge friends in a side-by-side dash to the finish. With delicious new food and drinks and surprises around every corner, there’s always a fresh reason to make a splash at Aquatica.

Adventure Island

Adventure Island® is Tampa Bay’s premier water park, featuring exhilarating water slides, a 17,000 square-foot wave pool and family attractions in 30 acres of tropical surroundings. At Tampa's Island Paradise guests can dig their toes into the sand or relax in lounge chairs or a private cabana. Adventure Island is home to thrilling slides such as Wahoo! Remix, Rapids Racer, Solar Vortex®, Vanish Point™, Caribbean Corkscrew® and Colossal Curl™, and an all-new interactive splash and play zone, Shaka-Laka Shores, among other family attractions.

King Spa and Sauna

Modeled after traditional Korean spas, King Spa and Sauna houses nine distinct therapy rooms, each of which specializes in treating a different form of ailment or anxiety. The Charcoal Room lines its walls with antibacterial briquettes, which can alleviate conditions such as eczema. The domed sauna in the Fire Sudatorium encircles entrants in dry-heat and oak-tree aromatherapy, whereas the low temperature of the Ice Room encourages blood flow to the chilled parts of the body. In the heated Base Rock Room, slabs of Siraka stone emit infrared rays, increasing circulation and lymphatic drainage.

You are able to store your items in a locker and use the wristband/key to pay for your desired treatments and food, even though you can also go the entire day without spending $ enjoying the various rooms. I especially enjoy the Korean silken tofu with beef in the food court. During the week is the best time to visit and plan for a few hours to leisurely explore. ❀❀❀

Sarah: It was an alright experience. There’s many sauna rooms with different themes- pretty cool. The hot tubs are small but feel really good. I didn’t try the food, but they have a sitting area playing sports on TV where people can talk. I slept over night in one of the women’s only rooms and it was a good sleep, although if I come again… I’m bringing a water bottle cause you really gotta stay hydrated.

❀❀❀

Christina: What a great way to enjoy a day off with a good friend! The premises were so well designed, different rooms for saunas, so very interesting. It feels rejuvenating; better circulatory conditioning for the whole body.
